The Alzheimer's Foundation of America's Educating America Tour is coming to Kansas tomorrow, June 15 at 10 a.m. CT. I encourage anyone who is interested to register by clicking below to learn more about Alzheimer’s disease and how we can work to end it: https://alzfdn.org/event/educating-america-tour-kansas/

Alzheimer's Foundation of America
15 hrs ·

Join AFA TOMORROW, June 15, from 10AM-12:45PM CT, for our Alzheimer’s & Caregiving Educational Conference: Kansas. This free virtual event connects Kansas residents with information about Alzheimer’s disease, brain health, caregiving and advance planning. All are welcome!

Learn more/register here: https://www.crowdcast.io/e/afas-kansas-virtual-2/register

Session topics include:
“Alzheimer’s Disease Update: From Treatment to Prevention”
Jeffrey M. Burns, MD, MS

“Elder Care and Asset Protection: Get the Care You Need without Draining Your Savings”
Rachel A. Spaethe, Esq.

“The Connection of Grief and Alzheimer’s”
Michelle Niedens, LSCSW & Eric Sigler, LMSW

For more information, visit www.alzfdn.org/tour
